    Title: Lifer of Appollonius of Tyana
Tags:
  - Union-Identity=Mysterium Magnum=Silence
Commentary: |
  He was a young man at the time of this remark. He forthwith accomplished a
  total silence which lasted five years. The most difficult part according to
  him was to refrain from refuting error when it reached his hearing.
---
On one occasion, Euxenus (a Pythagorean teacher at Aegae) asked Apollonius
why so noble a thinker as he and one who was master of a diction so fine and
nervous did not write a book. He replied： ‘I have not yet kept silence.'
